snippet: Rodney Alcala, a onetime contestant on “The Dating Game” who is on death row in California for five murders, admitted to killing two women in Manhattan in 1971 and 1977.
abstract: Rodney Alcala, a onetime contestant on The Dating Game who is on death row in California for five murders,  pleads guilty in Manhattan to killing two women in the city in 1971 and 1977.
lead_paragraph: Rodney Alcala, a onetime contestant on “The Dating Game” who is on death row in California for five murders, admitted to killing two women in Manhattan in 1971 and 1977.

headline.seo: Rodney Alcala Admits to Killing 2 in New York in the ’70s
headline.main: Convicted Killer Pleads Guilty to 2 New York Murders
